Six Bay Area counties have issued orders requiring face coverings in public to reduce the spread of the coronavirus.
Fremont: The East Bay city of Fremont is requiring workers and customers at essential businesses to wear face coverings amid the COVID-19 emergency.
Children over the age of 2 are being asked to wear face coverings.